libellum: this schedule (brevia- rium totius imperii) was one of three papers which were deposited by Augustus, together with his tes· tament, with the vestal virgins (Suet. Oct. 101). regna: probably countries like Cappadocia and Mauretania, still in name independent kingdoms‚ al- though ready to be incorporated in the empire as soon as the occasion should come.
